      <text xml:space="preserve">&lt;div style=&quot;float:right&quot;&gt;[[Image:Map of Brunei Demis.png|thumb|150px]]&lt;/div&gt;
{{Unreferenced|date=October 2009}}
[[Brunei]] is in [[Southeastern Asia]], bordering the [[South China Sea]] and [[Malaysia]].  Its geographical coordinates are {{Coord|4|30|N|114|40|E|}}.

Brunei shares a {{convert|481.3|km|mi|2|abbr=on}} [[Brunei-Malaysia Border|border]] with [[Malaysia]] and has a {{convert|161|km|mi|2|abbr=on}} coastline.

== Climate ==
''See also: [[Brunei#Climate|Climate]]''

The [[climate]] in Brunei is Hot, wet, cool and warm tropical and humid subtropical at higher altitudes with heavy rainfall. Bandar Seri Begawan's climate is tropical equatorial with two seasons. Dry season is extremely hot ({{convert|24|to|36|C|F|1|abbr=on|disp=/}}. Wet or rainy season is generally warm and wet ({{convert|20|to|28|C|F|1|abbr=on|disp=/}}). Most of the country is a flat [[coastal plain]] with [[mountain]]s in the east and hilly lowland in the west.  The lowest point is at [[sea level]] and the highest is [[Bukit Pagon]] ({{convert|1850|m|ft|0|abbr=on|disp=/}}).

=== Climatic regions ===
*[[Brunei-Muara District]] and [[Bandar Seri Begawan]] are humid tropical on the coastal and lower altitude north and Humid subtropical in central Brunei-Muara District. (20 to 36 degrees)

*[[Tutong District]] is [[Tropical]], Hot on the north and warm on the south. (22 to 32 degrees)

*[[Belait District]] is [[Tropical]], Hot on the north and slight warm on the south. (25 to 37 degrees)

*[[Temburong District]] is [[Humid subtropical]] on the higher altitude south and humid tropical on the coastal and lower altitude north. (18 to 29 degrees)

== Natural resources ==
Natural resources include [[petroleum]], [[natural gas]] and [[timber]].

