==Political pressure groups==
[[Burkinabé General Confederation of Labor]] or CGTB; [[Burkinabé Movement for Human Rights]] or HBDHP; [[Group of 14 February]]; [[National Confederation of Burkinabé Workers]] or CNTB; [[National Organization of Free Unions]] or ONSL; watchdog/political action groups throughout the country in both organizations and communities

==Administrative divisions==
Burkina Faso is divided into 13 regions and 45 provinces: 

'''[[Regions of Burkina Faso|Regions]]''': [[Boucle du Mouhoun Region|Boucle du Mouhoun]], [[Cascades Region|Cascades]], [[Centre Region (Burkina Faso)|Centre]], [[Centre-Est Region|Centre-Est]], [[Centre-Nord Region|Centre-Nord]], [[Centre-Ouest Region|Centre-Ouest]], [[Centre-Sud Region|Centre-Sud]], [[Est Region (Burkina Faso)|Est]], [[Hauts-Bassins Region|Hauts-Bassins]], [[Nord Region (Burkina Faso)|Nord]], [[Plateau-Central Region|Plateau-Central]], [[Sahel Region|Sahel]], [[Sud-Ouest Region (Burkina Faso)|Sud-Ouest]] 

'''[[Provinces of Burkina Faso|Provinces]]''': [[Bale Province, Burkina Faso|Balé]], [[Bam Province|Bam]], [[Banwa]], [[Bazega]], [[Bougouriba]], [[Boulgou]], [[Boulkiemde]], [[Comoe]], [[Ganzourgou]], [[Gnagna]], [[Gourma]], [[Houet]], [[Ioba]], [[Kadiogo]], [[Kenedougou (province)|Kenedougou]], [[Komondjari]], [[Kompienga]], [[Kossi]], [[Koulpelogo]], [[Kouritenga]], [[Kourweogo]], [[Leraba]], [[Loroum]], [[Mouhoun Province|Mouhoun]], [[Namentenga]], [[Nahouri]], [[Nayala]], [[Noumbiel]], [[Oubritenga]], [[Oudalan]], [[Passore]], [[Poni]], [[Sanguie]], [[Sanmatenga]], [[Seno]], [[Sissili]], [[Soum]], [[Sourou]], [[Tapoa]], [[Tuy (province)|Tuy]], [[Yagha]], [[Yatenga]], [[Ziro Province|Ziro]], [[Zondoma]], [[Zoundweogo]]

