      <text xml:space="preserve">{{wiktionary|biotic}}
'''Biotic''' means relating to, produced by, or caused by living [[organism]]s.
Biotic is a living component of a community; for example organisms, such as plants and animals. 
'''Biotic''' may also refer to:
*[[Life]], the condition of living organisms,
*[[Biology]], the study of life,
*[[Biotic material]], which is derived from living organisms,
*[[Biotic component]]s in ecology,
*[[Biotic potential]], an organism's reproductive capacity, or
*[[Biotic Baking Brigade]], an unofficial group of pie-throwing activists.
*[[Biotic community]], all the interacting organisms living together in a specific habitat

